# 1. What is CSS?

## Definition

CSS stands for **Cascading Style Sheets**.

CSS is used to design and style HTML pages.

HTML creates the structure of a webpage, while CSS makes it attractive.

---

## Real-Time Example

Think of building a house.

| House | Website |
|---------|----------|
| Foundation | HTML |
| Paint | CSS |
| Electricity | JavaScript |

Without paint,

the house works but does not look attractive.

Similarly,

without CSS,

the webpage works but looks plain.

---

## Answer

CSS is used to improve the appearance of a webpage.

---

