# 4. What is Bootstrap?

## Definition

Bootstrap is a free CSS framework.

It provides ready-made components such as:

- Buttons
- Forms
- Cards
- Navigation Bars
- Tables
- Alerts
- Responsive Layouts

---

## Answer

Bootstrap helps developers build professional websites quickly.

---

# 5. Why Bootstrap?

Without Bootstrap,

developers write large amounts of CSS.

With Bootstrap,

professional designs can be created using predefined classes.

---

## Example

Without Bootstrap

```css
button{
    background:blue;
    color:white;
}
```

With Bootstrap

```html
<button class="btn btn-primary">
Predict Salary
</button>
```

---

## Answer

Bootstrap reduces development time and improves design quality.

