# 8. Connecting CSS with HTML

Open

```text
index.html
```

Inside the `<head>` section,

add:

```html
<link
rel="stylesheet"
href="{{ url_for('static', filename='css/style.css') }}">
```

---

## Answer

`url_for()` tells Flask where the CSS file is located.

---

# 9. What is url_for()?

## Definition

`url_for()` generates the correct path for static files.

Example

```html
{{ url_for('static', filename='css/style.css') }}
```

Flask converts it into

```text
/static/css/style.css
```

---

## Answer

`url_for()` automatically generates file paths.

---

# 10. Adding Bootstrap

Inside `<head>`

add

```html
<link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.3/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
```

---

## Answer

Bootstrap styles are now available in your webpage.

